              <li>• Current statements for any other mortgages</li>
              <li>• Car loan / lease statements</li>
              <li>• Student loan statements</li>
              <li>• Credit card statements</li>
              <li>• Line of credit statements</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4" style="color: var(--primary)">10 Questions to Ask Your Mortgage Broker</h2>

        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-8 space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <li><strong>"What is the best rate you can get me right now — and from which lender?"</strong> — Don't just accept the first number. Ask them to justify it.</li>
          <li><strong>"What is the penalty structure on this product if I need to break mid-term?"</strong> — Critical, especially for fixed-rate products.</li>
          <li><strong>"Are you able to cover my switching costs through the new lender?"</strong> — Many lenders offer to cover discharge and legal fees. Ask.</li>
          <li><strong>"What prepayment privileges does this mortgage include?"</strong> — Understand your ability to pay down principal extra.</li>
          <li><strong>"Is this mortgage portable if I sell and buy a new property?"</strong> — Important if you might move during the term.</li>
          <li><strong>"What term length do you recommend given current rates and my situation?"</strong> — Get their professional opinion, not just options.</li>
          <li><strong>"Is this a standard charge or a collateral charge mortgage?"</strong> — Affects your flexibility at the next renewal.</li>
          <li><strong>"How are you compensated by the lender on this deal?"</strong> — A transparent broker will tell you.</li>
          <li><strong>"What lenders did you compare to arrive at this recommendation?"</strong> — Ensure they've done comprehensive shopping.</li>
          <li><strong>"What should I be doing now to improve my position before the next renewal in 3–5 years?"</strong> — A great broker thinks long-term with you.</li>
        </ol>

